review_blob: Poured from bottle, pours a cloudy coppery colour with nice off white/tan foamy head. Aroma of hops as you come to expect from ipas taste is a slightly different with the use rakau hops but a nice hoppy beer which isnt an over powering as some imperial ipas, cant wait for the 2011 brew to come out

330ml bottle poured into glass, pours a coppery amber colour with a medium sized off white head. a burnt/smokey taste with a hint of cinnamon coming through. a great amber ale maybe one of the best ive had
poured from can into glass. pour a slightly cloudy amber colour with a foam white head. a pine grassy hop aroma and taste to match. a good pale ale especially from a can

Bottle poured into glass. pours a dark chocolate colour with a thick creamy chocolate colour head. the aroma and taste of coffee and chocolate a you expect from a porter. another great beer from the guys at Flying Dog

650ml bottle, pours a dark amber coppery colour with a medium sized offwhite/creamy colour head. it has your usual hoppy ipa aroma and taste but i perfer a more hoppier ipa than this one has but its a very enjoyable brew

Day of release on tap at the local taphouse darlinghurst. A great hop/floral aroma and taste to match, pours a nice coppery colour with a thin white head. A fantastic IPA wish theyd add this to there regular line-up

pours a copper brown colour with a nice cream/off-white head. a malty/, nutty taste with hoppy bitterness after taste. not a big fan of brown ale especially the UK ones but i really enjoyed drinking this version from the little creatures boys
beer_name: Little Creatures Single Batch Brown Ale

review_blob: pours a clear amber colour with nice lasting creamy head. a fruity hoppy aroma and taste to match. not the best ipa ive had but a very enjoyable beer

another great beer beer from sierra nevada. pours a cloudy amber colour with a nice off white head. a citrus / resin hoppy taste with a hint of caramel flavour in the background. this is a great beer beer and recommend having one
my all time fav pale ale, just wish it was available more in australia. a floral  citris aroma and taste, its has goldern cloudy appearance with a nice white head
love this, every time i have it just keeps getting better. a chocolate malty aroma and taste with slight hint of cherry.
pours a nice golden colour with thin white head. a light grassy taste with a slight bitterness thrown in. another great beer from the flying dog boys
beer_name: Flying Dog Tire Bite Golden Ale

review_blob: one of New Zealands finest. starts off with that floral aroma, copper colour when poured and nice whiteish colour head, a very hoppy taste. just an awesome beer
The moment you knock the top off the aroma hits you and its a great aroma which is back up when you taste it. the hops and a slight malt taste make this a great IPA

Great beer for a summer arvo out in the beer garden. it has slight fruity aroma and taste with a bit of hoppiness thrown in, a great beer which is not as powerfull as its big brother (Alpha pale ale) but i perfer it to the Alpha pale ale
beer_name: Matilda Bay Fat Yak Pale Ale

review_blob: One of my favourate pale ales, great taste thats not to hoppy or over an powering bitterness. its a great beer beer for kicking back in the sun and enjoying a few quiet ones
